init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the 92nd little pig was like, "no, dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'm not going to eat you if you tell me."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the 92nd little pig said, "I found it in the desert."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the wolf was like, "dude, I'm not going to eat you if you tell me where in the desert you found it."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the 92nd little pig said, "I found it in the desert near the nuclear testing grounds."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf said, "I'm not going to eat you if you tell me what you mean by 'pig costume.'"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the 92nd little pig said, "I mean you should dress up like a pig."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the 92nd little pig said, "I mean that you should make a costume to pretend that you're a pig."

actions.text: He saw a bunch of pigs and a pig in a lab coat.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Welcome to the nuclear testing grounds.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Now I'm going to eat all of you pigs!"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was so happy because he was able to save all of the pigs and the wolf was dead.
